{"name": "odoo-addon-stock-pull-list", "metadata": {"name": "odoo-addon-stock-pull-list", "version": "16.0.1.0.0.5", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Framework :: Odoo", "Framework :: Odoo :: 16.0", "License :: OSI Approved :: GNU Affero General Public License v3", "Programming Language :: Python"], "home_page": "https://github.com/OCA/stock-logistics-warehouse", "license": "AGPL-3", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["odoo-addon-stock-free-quantity", "odoo"], "summary": "The pull list checks the stock situation and calculates needed quantities.", "upload_time": 1724387589}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  badge1: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/maturity-Beta-yellow.png\n    :alt: Beta\n    :target: https://odoo-community.org/page/development-status\n    ```\n  badge2: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/licence-AGPL--3-blue.png\n    :alt: 'License: AGPL-3'\n    :target: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0-standalone.html\n    ```\n  badge3: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/github-OCA%2Fstock--logistics--warehouse-lightgray.png?logo=github\n    :alt: OCA/stock-logistics-warehouse\n    :target: https://github.com/OCA/stock-logistics-warehouse/tree/16.0/stock_pull_list\n    ```\n  badge4: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/weblate-Translate%20me-F47D42.png\n    :alt: Translate me on Weblate\n    :target: https://translation.odoo-community.org/projects/stock-logistics-warehouse-16-0/stock-logistics-warehouse-16-0-stock_pull_list\n    ```\n  badge5: |-\n    ```{image} https://img.shields.io/badge/runboat-Try%20me-875A7B.png\n    :alt: Try me on Runboat\n    :target: https://runboat.odoo-community.org/builds?repo=OCA/stock-logistics-warehouse&target_branch=16.0\n    ```\n  maintainer-LoisRForgeFlow: |-\n    ```{image} https://github.com/LoisRForgeFlow.png?size=40px\n    :alt: LoisRForgeFlow\n    :target: https://github.com/LoisRForgeFlow\n    ```\n---\n\n# Stock Pull List\n\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n% !! This file is generated by oca-gen-addon-readme !!\n% !! changes will be overwritten.                   !!\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n% !! source digest: sha256:f598f1bcefb9fd22bccb581da3f9ad01160129c693f4aa9493accd478543b61a\n% !!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!\n\n{{ badge1 }} {{ badge2 }} {{ badge3 }} {{ badge4 }} {{ badge5 }}\n\nThe pull list checks the stock situation at the given location and calculates\nthe shortfall quantities (quantity needed to cover all needs) for products.\nProcurements can be created for these shortfall quantities.\n\n**Table of contents**\n\n```{contents}\n:local: true\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nTo use the module follow the next steps:\n\n1. Go to *Inventory > Operations > Generate Pull List*.\n2. Select the location to get the pull list from. Add some filtering if needed.\n3. Click on Prepare. You will now see the pull list with all the needs.\n4. Adjust grouping options as needed. This will generate different procurement\n   groups.\n5. Click on *Procure*.\n\nWizard can be also launched through a server action on multiple transfers; this is to allow user to select with ease which transfers to include in the pull list. Please note that:\n\n1. To select a transfer to be included in pull list through server action, you first need to go to its operation type and enable field \"Allow pull list server action\".\n2. Only transfers with the same Source Location can be selected at one time.\n\n## Known issues / Roadmap\n\n- In wizard, when `exclude_reserved` is selected, handle partially available moves.\n- Use sequence numbering for procurement groups made from pull list.\n- Return a pull list summary at the end.\n\n## Bug Tracker\n\nBugs are tracked on [GitHub Issues](https://github.com/OCA/stock-logistics-warehouse/issues).\nIn case of trouble, please check there if your issue has already been reported.\nIf you spotted it first, help us to smash it by providing a detailed and welcomed\n[feedback](https://github.com/OCA/stock-logistics-warehouse/issues/new?body=module:%20stock_pull_list%0Aversion:%2016.0%0A%0A**Steps%20to%20reproduce**%0A-%20...%0A%0A**Current%20behavior**%0A%0A**Expected%20behavior**).\n\nDo not contact contributors directly about support or help with technical issues.\n\n## Credits\n\n### Authors\n\n- ForgeFlow\n\n### Contributors\n\n- Lois Rilo \\<<mailto:lois.rilo@forgeflow.com>>\n\n### Maintainers\n\nThis module is maintained by the OCA.\n\n```{image} https://odoo-community.org/logo.png\n:alt: Odoo Community Association\n:target: https://odoo-community.org\n```\n\nOCA, or the Odoo Community Association, is a nonprofit organization whose\nmission is to support the collaborative development of Odoo features and\npromote its widespread use.\n\nCurrent [maintainer](https://odoo-community.org/page/maintainer-role):\n\n{{ maintainer-LoisRForgeFlow }}\n\nThis module is part of the [OCA/stock-logistics-warehouse](https://github.com/OCA/stock-logistics-warehouse/tree/16.0/stock_pull_list) project on GitHub.\n\nYou are welcome to contribute. To learn how please visit <https://odoo-community.org/page/Contribute>.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "odoo.addons.stock_pull_list.models.stock_picking_type", "documentation": ["Copyright 2020-24 ForgeFlow, S.L.", "License AGPL-3.0 or later (https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl.html)."], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "odoo.addons.stock_pull_list.models.stock_picking_type.StockPickingType", "bases": ["models.Model"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "odoo.addons.stock_pull_list.models.stock_picking_type.StockPickingType._inherit", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "odoo.addons.stock_pull_list.models.stock_picking_type.StockPickingType.allow_pull_list_server_action", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "odoo.addons.stock_pul